The police on Friday arraigned a 31-year-old electrician, Huber Buton, for allegedly stealing his employer’s clothes and shoes worth N6,2 million, at the Tinubu Chief Magistrates’ Court in Lagos. The police charged Buton with conspiracy and theft. He pleaded not guilty.to the charges. The prosecution counsel, ASP Edet Okoi, told the court that the defendant committed the offence in August at No.14, Adeyemi Lawson, Ikoyi, Lagos. Okoi alleged that the accused stole clothes and shoes valued at N6.2 million belonging to his employer, Mrs. Aisha Samaila. Court convicts six yahoo boys in Calabar Chief Magistrate Tajudeen Elias granted the defendant bail in the sum of N1 million with two sureties in like sum. He adjourned the case till October 17, for mention. (NAN)  Vanguard News The police on Friday arraigned a 31-year-old electrician, Huber Buton, who allegedly stole his employer’s clothes and shoes worth N6.2 million, in a Tinubu Chief Magistrates’ Court in Lagos. The police charged Buton with conspiracy and theft. He pleaded not guilty. The Prosecution Counsel, ASP Edet Okoi, told the court… September 27, 2019 In "Crime Alert" The police on Wednesday arraigned a 26-year-old driver, Musa Habila in a Kaduna Chief Magistrates’ Court over alleged theft of his employer’s Lexus Jeep. March 14, 2018 In "News" A 20-year-old househelp , Faith Edeh, who was alleged to have stolen her employer’s jewellery and other items worth N20 million, was yesterday arraigned before an Igbosere Magistrates’ Court in Lagos. Edeh was arraigned alongside one Peter Obah, 37, the agent that brought her to her employer. January 23, 2016 In "News"